 that satisfy  \n−𝑥+2𝑦+3𝑧=3, 2𝑥−𝑦+2𝑧=5 and 𝑥+𝑦+𝑧=4 \n \nQuestion 0 4 \n \nUse a matrix method to find the numbers 𝑥,𝑦,𝑧 that satisfy  \n𝑥+𝑦+𝑧=4,  2𝑥−𝑦+2𝑧=5 and −𝑥+2𝑦+3𝑧=3 \n \nQuestion 0 5 \n \nExpress the following system of equations in matrix form  and solve it using a matrix method.  \n \n   4𝑥+𝑦−2𝑧=4 \n   2𝑥+3𝑦−2𝑧=4 \n   2𝑥+5𝑦+2𝑧=8 \n \n  \n 2 Question 0 6 \n \nExpress the following system of equations in matrix form  and solve it using a matrix method.  \n \n   2𝑥+𝑦−𝑧=4 \n   𝑥+3𝑦−𝑧=4 \n   𝑥+5𝑦+𝑧=8 \n \nQuestion 0 7 \n \nExpress the following system of equations in matrix form, and solve it using a matrix method.  \n \n   𝑥+𝑦+3𝑧=6 \n   2𝑥+𝑦+𝑧=1 \n       −5𝑥−2𝑦+2𝑧=7 \n \nQuestion 08 \n \nExpress the following system of equations in matrix form  and solve it using a matrix method.  \n \n   𝑥−𝑦+𝑧=2 \n   3𝑥+𝑦−2𝑧=0 \n   5𝑥−2𝑦−𝑧=1 \n \nQuestion 09 \n \nUse a matrix method to determine the numbers 𝑥, 𝑦, 𝑧 satisfying  \n \n(1−2−1\n−2−35\n311) (𝑥\n𝑦\n𝑧) = (4\n9\n2) \n \n \nQuestion 10 \n \nUse a matrix method to determine the numbers 𝑥, 𝑦, 𝑧 satisfying  \n \n(12−1\n−235\n3−11) (𝑥\n𝑦\n𝑧) = (4\n9\n2) 1 Date: - 8th October, 2025  \n \n \nStudent Registration Number  (SRN)  Name with Initials  \n  \n \nDepartment of Computational Mathematics  \nCM 2121:  Foundation of Mathematical Methods  \nChapter 1:  Matrices & Linear Equations  \nTutorial  02 \n \nQuestion 01  \n \nShow that the following system of equations has a solution for all values of 𝑎, provided a certain \nrelationship between 𝑐 and 𝑏 holds. (You should determine what this relationship is). Find all solutions, \nin terms of 𝑎 and 𝑏, when the system has solutions.  \n \n𝑥−𝑦+2𝑧=𝑎 \n2𝑥−3𝑦+4𝑧=𝑏 \n4𝑥+6𝑧=15𝑎 \n𝑥+3𝑦+8𝑧=𝑐 \n \nQuestion 0 2 \n \n \nShow that the following system of equations has a solution for all values of 𝑎, provided a certain \nrelationship between 𝑐 and 𝑏 holds. (You should determine what this relationship is). Find all solutions, \nin terms of 𝑎 and 𝑏, when the system does have solutions.  \n \n𝑥+𝑦+𝑧=𝑎 \n2𝑥+3𝑦+2𝑧=𝑏 \n4𝑥+3𝑧=15𝑎 \n𝑥−3𝑦+4𝑧=𝑐 \n \n \n \n  \n 2 Question 0 3 \n \nUse a matrix method to find all solutions to the following system of equations  \n \n \n2𝑥−𝑦+𝑧=4 \n−𝑥+3𝑦+2𝑧=3 \n𝑥+2𝑦+3𝑧=7 \n𝑥−2𝑦−𝑧=−1 \n \nQuestion 0 4 \n \nConsider the following system of equations.  \n \n𝑥+𝑦−3𝑧=4 \n2𝑥−𝑦+𝑧=3 \n𝑥+4𝑦+𝑎𝑧=𝑏 \n \nUse matrix methods to determine what values 𝑎 and 𝑏 must take if this system is consistent and has \ninfinitely many solutions.  \n \nWhat must the value of 𝑎 not be if the system has precisely one solution?  \n \nWhat can be said about 𝑎 and 𝑏 if the system has no solutions?  \n \nQuestion 0 5 \n \nUse a matrix method to find all solutions to the following system of equations  \n \n2𝑥+𝑦−𝑧=2 \n𝑥+3𝑦+2𝑧=6 \n−𝑥+2𝑦+3𝑧=4 \n𝑥+8𝑦+7𝑧=16 \n \nQuestion 0 6 \n \nConsider the following system of equations.  \n \n𝑥−𝑦+2𝑧=4 \n3𝑥−𝑦−𝑧=0 \n𝑥+𝑦+𝑎𝑧=𝑏 \n \nUse matrix methods to determine what values 𝑎 and 𝑏 must take if this system is consistent and has \ninfinitely many solutions.  \n \nWhat must the value of 𝑎 not be if the system has precisely one solution?  \n \nWhat can be said about 𝑎 and 𝑏 if the system has no solutions?   \n 3 Question 07 \n \nUsing matrix methods, throughout, show that there is just one value of 𝑘 for which the following system \nof linear equations has more than one solution, and determine all the solutions when 𝑘 takes this value. \nWhat is the solution for other values of 𝑘? \n \n2𝑥+𝑦+𝑧=4 \n6𝑥−𝑦−𝑧=4 \n−4𝑥+𝑘𝑦+6𝑧=8 \n \nQuestion 08 \n \nUsing matrix methods, throughout, show that there is just one value of 𝑘 for which the following system \nof linear equations has more than one solution, and determine all the solutions when 𝑘 takes this value. \nWhat is the solution for other values of 𝑘? \n \n𝑥−𝑦+𝑧=2 \n3𝑥+𝑦−𝑧=2 \n−2𝑥+𝑘𝑦+6𝑧=4 \n \nQuestion 09 \n \nUsing a matrix method, find all the solutions to the following system of equations:  \n \n2𝑥1−𝑥2+𝑥3=4 \n𝑥1−3𝑥2+2𝑥3=4 \n3𝑥1+𝑥2=4 \n \nQuestion 1 0 \n \nUsing a matrix method, find all the solutions to t