unction\r\nCLO 3: Apply concepts of matrices in analysing systems\r\nof linearequationsalgorithmically\r\nCLO 4: Apply concepts of vectors and matrix algebra to\r\nsolverealworldproblems\r\nCLO 5: Model real world problems using theconceptsof\r\nderivativesand integrals\r\n3Outline Syllabus\r\nLimits and Derivatives\r\nIntegration\r\nVector Algebra\r\nMatrix Algebra\r\n4 CM 2121  \r\n \r\n \r\n Page 1 of 2 UNIVERSITY OF MORATUWA  \r\nFaculty of Information Technology  \r\nDepartment of Computational Mathematics  \r\n \r\nBachelor of Science  Honours in Information Technology & Management  \r\nBatch 23 - Semester 3 - Assignment  1 \r\n \r\n        CM 2121  – FOUNDATION  OF MATHEMATIC AL METHODS  \r\n \r\nTime Allowed: 1 hour                                 Octo ber 2025 \r\n \r\n \r\nINSTRUCTIONS TO CANDIDATES  \r\n \r\n1. This examination paper contains 2 question s on 2 pages (including th e cover page) . \r\n \r\n2. The total marks obtainable for this examination is 100 . \r\n \r\n3. This is a close d-book examination.  \r\n \r\n4. Answer ALL  questions.  \r\n \r\n5. All the necessary steps  for the answers should be clearly indicated  (the rough work should not be \r\ninclude d together with the answer s). \r\n \r\n6. Rough work sheets may be attached  separately . \r\n \r\n7. Calculators are NOT ALLOWED . \r\n \r\n \r\n \r\n \r\n \r\n \r\n \r\n \r\n \r\n \r\n \r\n \r\n \r\n \r\n \r\n \r\n \r\n \r\nContinued…  \r\nCM 2121  \r\n \r\n \r\n Page 2 of 2 Question 01  \r\n \r\nSolve the following system of linear equations by using  elementary row operations : \r\n \r\n \r\n \r\n \r\n \r\nQuestion 02  \r\n \r\nUse elementary row operations  to find all solutions to the following system of linear \r\nequations : \r\n \r\n \r\n \r\n \r\n \r\n \r\nQuestion 0 3 \r\n \r\nConsider the following system of linear equations : \r\n \r\n \r\n \r\n \r\n \r\n(a) Determine what values 𝑎 and 𝑏 must take if this system is consistent and has \r\ninfinitely many solutions.  \r\n \r\